{
  "texts": [
    "The abnormality with the largest number of GT bounding boxes was nodules, up to 45,977.",
    "To the best of our knowledge, the CXR-AL14 dataset is the largest CXR dataset with bounding boxes for 14 common abnormalities.",
    "Based on the dataset, the YOLOX model was trained and tuned for the identification and localization of multiple abnormalities at a ratio of 9:1, and evaluated on",
    "b a CXR-AL14 dataset (Training and tuning) Annotated by expert group Annotated by human-in-the-loop 6,000 CXRs Recombination test dataset 165,988 CXRs Held-out test dataset Included CXRs Annotate and screen Measure and screen 10,000 CXRs 12,000 CXRs Included CXRs Training and tuning dataset Attention U-net to segment double lungs and heart, followed by CTR calculation 2,000 CXRs Test dataset YOLOX model to identify and localize 14 chest abnormalities 2,800 CXRs selected randomly Atelectasis Calcification Consolidation Effusion Emphysema Fibrosis Fracture Mass Nodule Pleural thickening Pneumatosis Pneumothorax Postoperative metal Venipuncture Model vs Radiologists Multicenter validation Prospective validation CTR calculation Multicenter validation Prospective validation Internal validation held-out, multicentre and prospective test datasets.",
    "Manufacturer and device information for each dataset is displayed in Supplementary Table 1."
  ]
}